Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharpish turn. Clay near fine light buff-brown. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Eukleitos
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0939)
